{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "A precise measurement of the vector and axialvector form factors difference F V \u2212 F A in the K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03b3 decay is presented. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "About 95K events of K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03b3 are selected in the OKA experiment. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The result is F V \u2212 F A = 0.134 \u00b1 0.021(stat) \u00b1 0.027(syst). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Both errors are smaller than in the previous F V \u2212 F A measurements.",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Radiative kaon decays are sensitive to hadronic weak currents in low-energy region and provide a good testing for the chiral perturbation theory (\u03c7 PT ). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The amplitude of the K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03b3 decay includes two terms: internal bremsstra-hlung (IB) and structure dependent term (SD) [1]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 127,
                    "end": 130,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "IB contains radiative corrections for K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc decay. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "SD is sensitive to the electroweak structure of the kaon.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The differential decay rate can be written in terms of standard kinematic variables x = 2E * \u03b3 /M K and y = 2E * \u03bc /M K [2], which are proportional to the photon E * \u03b3 and muon E * \u03bc energy in the kaon rest frame (M K is the kaon mass). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 120,
                    "end": 123,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "It includes IB, SD \u00b1 terms and their interference INT \u00b1 . ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The SD \u00b1 and INT \u00b1 contributions are determined by two form factors F V and F A .",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "V. K. Semenov: Deceased.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "a e-mail: kravtsov@inr.ru",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The general formula for the decay rate is as follows:",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "where",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "and",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Here \u03b1 is the fine struc- ) and \u0393 K \u03bc2 is the K \u03bc2 decay width. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 1 shows the kinematic distribution for IB, INT \u2212 , INT + , SD \u2212 and SD + . ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 8,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Figure 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The main goal of the analysis is to measure F V \u2212 F A by extracting the INT \u2212 term. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Other terms are either suppressed by backgrounds or give negligible contribution to the total decay rate with respect to IB. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In the lowest order of \u03c7 PT O( p 4 ) F V and F A are constant and F V \u2212 F A = 0.052 [2]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 84,
                    "end": 87,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The first measurement of F V \u2212 F A was made by the ISTRA+ experiment:",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The OKA setup, Fig. 2, is a double magnetic spectrometer. ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 15,
                    "end": 21,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "More details can be found in [5]. ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 29,
                    "end": 32,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The data acquisition system of the OKA setup [6] operates at \u223c 25 kHz event rate with the mean event size of \u223c 4 kByte.",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 45,
                    "end": 48,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The OKA beam is a separated secondary beam of the U-70 Proton Synchrotron of NRC \"Kurchatov Institute\"-IHEP, Protvino [7]. ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 118,
                    "end": 121,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[7]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "RF-separation with the Panofsky scheme [8] is implemented. ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 39,
                    "end": 42,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[8]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The beam contains up to 12.5% of kaons with an intensity of about 5 \u00d7 10 5 kaons per 3 sec U-70 spill. ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The beam momentum was 17.7 GeV/c during the data taking period used for the analysis (November 2012). ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The present study uses about half of the statistics collected in 2012, where 504M events were recorded. ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Another half was taken with a thin copper target inside the decay volume to study the kaon interactions with nucleus. ",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "It needs a special consideration, which could be done eventually.",
            "section": "OKA detector and separated kaon beam",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The following trigger is used for the analysis:",
            "section": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "is a coincidence of four beam scintillation counters,\u010c 1,2threshold Cherenkov counters (\u010c 1 selects pions,\u010c 2 -pions and kaons), S bk (\"beam killer\") -two scintillation counters on the beam axis after the magnet aimed to suppress undecayed beam particles. ",
            "section": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The analog amplitude sum in the GAMS-2000 is required to be higher than E G AM S (E G AM S is chosen to be above the average MIP energy deposit). ",
            "section": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 32,
                    "end": 42,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "GAMS-2000",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The 10 times prescaled minimum bias trigger S bk is used for the trigger efficiency measurement trig = (T G AM S \u2229 T kaon )/T kaon (Fig. 3).",
            "section": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 131,
                    "end": 138,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "(Fig. 3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This trigger efficiency was applied during the Monte Carlo (MC) simulation.",
            "section": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "To select the decay channel the following requirements are applied:",
            "section": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "-1 parent K + track; -1 secondary track identified as muon in GAMS-2000, GDA-100 and \u03bcC; -1 electromagnetic shower in GAMS-2000 with energy E tot > 1 GeV not associated with charged track; -GS energy deposition E G S < 10 MeV ; -EGS energy deposition E EG S < 100 MeV ; -Decay vertex inside the decay volume DV.",
            "section": "Trigger streams and primary selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 62,
                    "end": 66,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "GAMS",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s2"
                },
                {
                    "start": 118,
                    "end": 128,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "GAMS-2000",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Event selection",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The main background to the K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03b3 decay comes from 2 decay modes: K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03c0 0 (K \u03bc3) and K + \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 0 (K 2\u03c0 ) with one \u03b3 lost from \u03c0 0 \u2192 \u03b3 \u03b3 decay and \u03c0 misidentified as \u03bc. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "Additional contribution at y > 1 is given by the decay mode K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc with an accidental \u03b3 . ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "At low y values there is a small contribution from the",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The MC simulation of the OKA setup is done within the GEANT3 framework [9]. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 71,
                    "end": 74,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Signal and background events are weighted according to corresponding matrix elements. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The 22M signal and 624M background MC events are generated.",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03b3 event selection strategy is based on the ISTRA+ approach [4]. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 77,
                    "end": 80,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "[4]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Signal extraction procedure starts with dividing all kinematic (x, y) region into strips in x with \u0394x = 0.05 width. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The following steps are implemented for each x-strip: -Plot the distribution of the events over y.",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "-Select the signal region by a cut y min < y < y max and fill cos \u03b8 * \u03bc\u03b3 plot, where \u03b8 * \u03bc\u03b3 is an angle between \u03bc and \u03b3 in the kaon rest frame. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "y min and y max are selected from the maximization of signal significance defined as S/ \u221a S + B where S is the signal and B is the background. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "For example, the selected cuts for the left plot of Fig. 4 are: y min = 0.85, y max = 1.0.",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 52,
                    "end": 58,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_2",
                    "text": "Fig. 4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "-Apply a cut on cos \u03b8 * \u03bc\u03b3 to futher reject the background. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "For the middle plot of Fig. 4 the cut is cos \u03b8 * \u03bc\u03b3 > \u22120.2. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 23,
                    "end": 29,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_2",
                    "text": "Fig. 4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Plot the distribution of the selected events over m k . ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "m 2 k = (P \u03bc + P \u03bd + P \u03b3 ) 2 , where P \u03bc , P \u03bd , P \u03b3 are 4-momenta of decay particles in the laboratory frame, p \u03bd = p K \u2212 p \u03bc \u2212 p \u03b3 , E \u03bd = |p \u03bd |. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 27,
                    "end": 28,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "m k peaks at the kaon mass for the signal.",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "-The last step is a simultaneous fit of all 3 histograms (y, cos \u03b8 * \u03bc\u03b3 , m k ) with the MINUIT tool [10] where the signal and backgrounds normalization factors are the fit parameters.",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 101,
                    "end": 105,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[10]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 89,
                    "end": 96,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MINUIT",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For the correct estimation of the statistical error \u03c3 ex p , only the m k histogram is used. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The MINOS program [10] is run once with the initial parameter values equal to those obtained in the simultaneous fit. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 18,
                    "end": 22,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[10]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 10,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MINOS",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Statistical errors were extracted from the MINOS output. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 43,
                    "end": 48,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MINOS",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 5 shows the selected kinematic region for the extraction of the INT \u2212 term. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 8,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_3",
                    "text": "Figure 5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For the further analysis 10 xstrips were selected in the 0.1 < x < 0.6 region. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The y-width varies from 0.12 to 0.30 inside x-strips.",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The result of the simultaneous fit for the strip 2 (0.15 < x < 0.2) is shown in Fig. 4. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 80,
                    "end": 86,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_2",
                    "text": "Fig. 4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Both signal and background shapes are taken from the MC simulation. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The total normalization of the MC to data is made to the K \u03bc3 decay at y < 0.6, where the contribution of other backgrounds is very small. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The relative normalization of other backgrounds is done according to their branching ratios. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "For the K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03b3 decay, only IB term is included in the simultaneous fit. ",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The simultaneous fit gives a reasonable agreement between data and MC with \u03c7 2 from 1.3 to 1.7 for different x-strips.",
            "section": "Event selection",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "For each x-strip the number of signal events N Data is extracted from the simultaneous fit and the IB event number N I B is obtained from MC. ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "Their ratio is plotted as a function of x (Fig. 6). ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 42,
                    "end": 49,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_4",
                    "text": "(Fig. 6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For the signal containing IB only this ratio would be equal to 1. ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "It is the case for small x, when the IB is dominating and INT \u2212 is negligible. ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "For large x the INT \u2212 term gives significant negative contribution resulting in smaller values of N Data /N I B .",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "is a similar distribution for the same MC sample, but with the weights f I B (x true , y true ). ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 28,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "Here x true , y true are \"true\" MC values of x and y.",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 28,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The result of the fit is F V \u2212 F A = 0.134\u00b10.021. ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The normalization factor is p 0 = 1.000\u00b10.007. ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The total number of selected K + \u2192 \u03bc + \u03bd \u03bc \u03b3 decay events is 95428 \u00b1 309.",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "In the next order \u03c7 PT O( p 6 ) F V linearly depends on the momentum transfer q 2 [11] with the following parametrization [12]:  (Fig. 7). ",
            "section": "F V \u2212 F A calculation",
            "paragraph_rank": 30,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 82,
                    "end": 86,
                    "type": "bibr",
